commit.message: Change version number to 0.5.

Improve handling of unreadable files (#44)

* Fix Python 2 import-finding bug.

The second argument to find_module should be a list of strings:
https://docs.python.org/2/library/imp.html#imp.find_module

* Improve unreadable file handling.

* Catch all resolve_import exceptions immediately. This allows us
  to correctly mark a particular import as unresolved rather than
  marking the importing module as unreadable.
* Don't prune the unreadable file from the graph. This gives
  callers more flexibility in handling syntax errors.

* Don't require a '.py' extension.

commit.message: Handle `from . import Symbol` style of relative imports.
Update the version number in setup.py.
Update CHANGELOG with --trim change.

Add an option to trim the deps of builtin and system files. (#32)

Adds a --trim option that will cause
DependencyGraph.add_file_recursive to stop recursing once it hits
a resolved.(Builtin|System) file. The purpose of this option is to
generate cleaner output for tools like pytype-all, which doesn't
care about the dependencies of pip-installed modules.

Update import_finder to be compatible with the new pytype release. (#31)

Pytype is now able to tell whether a Python version imports importlib
or imp, so it was generating name errors on the other import.

Simplify subprocess logic. (#30)

While playing around with subprocess and pytype-all, I noticed that importlab's
use of subprocess could be simplified. Since there was only one function left
in runner.py after my change, I moved it to utils.py and added a test.

Also fixed some flake8 errors.

All existing tests still pass.
